e recovered, grew into a statesman, and eventually became a prime victor of the Second World War. Such are the ironies of history; John Lukacs paints them with a shining narrative skill.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aWorld War, 1939-1945xCampaignszRussia (Federation). 0aWorld War, 1939-1945xCampaignszSoviet Union. 0aWorld War, 1939-1945zGermany. 0aWorld War, 1939-1945zSoviet Union. 7aHISTORY / Europe / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030018093040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300180930423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300180930/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles